{{Infobox building | name = Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art | native_name = 福岡県立美術館 | image = Fukuoka Museum of Art.JPG | caption = | cost = | owner = | address = 5-2-1 Tenjin, [[Chūō-ku, Fukuoka|Chūō-ku]] | location_town = [[Fukuoka]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]] | location_country = [[Japan]] | coordinates = {{coord|33.597242|N|130.398750|E|display=title,inline|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | opened_date = 3 November 1985 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | architect = | architecture_firm = | url = {{homepage|http://fukuoka-kenbi.jp}} }}
{{nihongo|'''Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art'''|福岡県立美術館|Fukuoka kenritsu bijutsukan}} opened in [[Fukuoka]], Japan, in 1985. The collection focuses upon artists from [[Fukuoka Prefecture]] and [[Kyūshū]] more generally, and includes works by [[Harue Koga|Koga Harue]]. The Museum's precursor, the {{nihongo|Fukuoka Prefectural Cultural Hall|福岡県文化会館}}, which combined art museum with library, opened on 3 November 1964.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/museums/detail/577 |script-title=ja:福岡県立美術館 |trans-title=Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pref.fukuoka.lg.jp/uploaded/life/30205_16792407_misc.pdf |script-title=ja:新しい福岡県立美術館のあり方について |trans-title=A New Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Fukuoka Prefecture]] |page=10 |date=August 2008 |accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://fukuoka-kenbi.jp/about |script-title=ja:福岡県立美術館について |trans-title=About Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art |language=Japanese |publisher=Fukuoka Prefectural Museum of Art |accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref>
