{{Infobox musical artist | name = Watkins Family Hour | image = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | alt = | caption = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] | genre = [[Bluegrass music]], [[folk music]] | years_active = {{start date|2002}}–present | label = Family Hour Records | associated_acts = [[Nickel Creek]] | website = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} --> | current_members = [[Sara Watkins]], [[Sean Watkins]], [[Benmont Tench]], [[Greg Leisz]], [[Sebastian Steinberg]], [[Don Heffington]] | past_members = | module = | module2 = | module3 = }} '''Watkins Family Hour''' is a [[bluegrass music|bluegrass]] musical collaborative led by [[Sara Watkins|Sara]] and [[Sean Watkins]]. The group began in 2002 as a monthly, informal musical [[variety show]] with the Watkins siblings and their friends in the [[Los Angeles]] nightclub [[Largo (nightclub)|Largo]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/watkins-family-hour-mn0003401139/biography | title=Watkins Family Hour Biography | work=Allmusic | accessdate=1 October 2016 | author=Monger, Timothy}}</ref> Their eponymous debut album, which consists entirely of covers,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.npr.org/2015/07/15/422555833/first-listen-watkins-family-hour-watkins-family-hour | title=Review: Watkins Family Hour, 'Watkins Family Hour' | work=NPR | date=15 July 2015 | accessdate=1 October 2016 | author=See, Elena}}</ref> was released on July 24, 2015 on Family Hour Records via [[Thirty Tigers]],<ref name=paste>{{cite web | url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2015/07/the-watkins-family-hour-the-watkins-family-hour.html | title=Watkins Family Hour: Watkins Family Hour Review | work=Paste Magazine | date=24 July 2015 | accessdate=1 October 2016 | author=Gleason, Holly}}</ref> and was produced by [[Sheldon Gomberg]].<ref name=metacritic>{{cite web | url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/watkins-family-hour/watkins-family-hour | title=Watkins Family Hour | work=Metacritic | accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref> In addition to the Watkins, musicians who performed on this album include [[Fiona Apple]], [[Lone Justice]]'s [[Don Heffington]], [[Benmont Tench]], [[Greg Leisz]], and [[Soul Coughing]]’s [[Sebastian Steinberg]].<ref name=paste/> According to [[Metacritic]], ''Watkins Family Hour'' received generally favorable reviews from critics; on the site, the album has a score of 76 out of 100, based on six reviews.<ref name=metacritic/>
